                            <comment id="14602436" author="dholmes" created="Mon, 7 Aug 2023 16:13:41 -0700"  >Yes it was an oversight on my part when fixing &lt;a href=&quot;https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8194309&quot; title=&quot;JNI handle allocation failure not reported correctly&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JDK-8194309&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JDK-8194309&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Usually passing NULL is a programming error in JNI and we don&amp;#39;t have to detect it, but not in this case.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Suggested fix:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
if (ret == nullptr &amp;amp;&amp;amp; !ref_handle().is_null()) {&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;THROW_OOP_(Universe::out_of_memory_error_c_heap(), nullptr);&lt;br/&gt;
}</comment>
